V8 is Google's open source JavaScript engine. 

V8 is written in C++ and is used in Google Chrome, the open source browser from
Google. 

V8 implements ECMAScript as specified in ECMA-262, 3rd edition, and runs on
Windows XP and Vista, Mac OS X 10.5 (Leopard), and Linux systems that use IA-32
or ARM processors. 

V8 can run standalone, or can be embedded into any C++ application. 

WWW:	http://code.google.com/p/v8/
